Hradec is a village and municipality (obec) located in the Havlíčkův Brod District within the Vysočina Region of the Czech Republic.
The municipality covers an area of 5.67 square kilometres (2.19 sq mi), and it has a population of 237 as of 28 August, 2006.
Hradec lies approximately 24 kilometres (15 mi) north-west of the municipality of Havlíčkův Brod, 41 km (25 mi) north-west of Jihlava, and 76 km (47 mi) south-east of Prague.